article.headline: High Point 87, Radford 84
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Arizona Reid had 24 points and 12 rebounds as High Point held on to beat Radford 87-84 in the first round of the Big South Conference tournament Tuesday night. High Point (16-11) led by 11 with 5:16 remaining, but Radford went on a 14-3 run capped off by Andre Bynum's 3-pointer that tied it at 81 with 55 seconds left. Issa Konare answered with a 3 of his own, and Akeem Scott's free throw with 12 seconds left put High Point up by four. Whit Holcomb-Faye hit a 3-pointer with 6 seconds left that made it 85-84, but Mike Jefferson was fouled and made both shots and Dan Ross' 3-pointer at the buzzer hit the glass and bounced off. Radford (16-13) jumped ahead by nine with 16:12 to go in the first half, but High Point went on a 19-0 run over the next five minutes that put the Panthers up by 10, at 26-16. Holcomb-Faye had back-to-back 3-pointers to spark a 12-2 Radford run that tied it at 28 with 8:25 left in the half. Holcomb-Faye's 3-pointer with 42 seconds left put the Highlanders up 42-39 at the half. Holcomb-Faye led Radford with 33 points, including six from beyond the arc. Chris Oliver had 16 for Radford, Bynum had 14 and Reggie McIntyre added 10. Mike Jefferson had 19 for High Point, Scott added 12 and Konare had 10 points and 10 rebounds.
